******
[3] Wisconsin (Walworth and Dane counties)
Date: Fri 7 Oct 2022
Source: Horse and Rider [abridged, edited]
https://horseandrider.com/news/hr-edcc-health-watch/two-horses-test-positive-for-strangles-in-wisconsin/


The Wisconsin Department of Agriculture, Trade and Consumer Protection confirmed 2 horses in Walworth and Dane counties positive for strangles.

On 29 Sep 2022, a 15-year-old Quarter Horse mare at a private facility in Dane County tested positive. She presented with a cough, fever, and nasal discharge beginning on 21 Sep 2022. She did not have a fever and is currently alive.

A 19-year-old Quarter Horse mare in Walworth County also tested positive. Voluntary quarantines are in place at both facilities.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Mahmoud Orabi

